title: Flying
analysis: Dreaming about flying over the sun often indicates optimism, enlightenment, and freedom. You may be feeling "on top of the world" in your waking life. This could mean that you have overcome major hurdles or challenges, and you're currently feeling liberated. Alternatively, dreaming of flying also symbolizes spiritual awareness; being over the sun may represent achieving higher levels of consciousness or spiritual insight. It's a positivity-fueled dream symbolizing growth, power, and the need for warmth, creativity, and inspiration in your life.

title: Pyramids
entry: Traveling through endless pyramid tunnels solving puzzles and fighting monsters.
analysis:
This dream signifies your current life journey. The pyramid itself is symbolic of stability and endurance, perhaps due to some challenges you're enduring or about to face. By traveling through the endless tunnels, it's a sign that your subconscious believes you are on a long and potentially complex journey.

The puzzles represent the various challenges or decisions you have to make in your life. These could be related to your personal or professional life. The fact that you're solving them in the dream suggests that you have the skills and resources required to overcome these issues.

Fighting monsters can be seen as a representation of your fears or obstacles. By fighting these monsters, it indicates that you are confronting your problems and fears directly rather than avoiding them. 

The nature of the monsters would provide more insight into what specific obstacles or fears you're dealing with. For example, if the monsters are people from your waking life, they may symbolize individuals with whom you have conflicts or difficulties.

Overall, this dream encourages inner strength, perseverance, problem-solving skills, and confronting fears. It might be pointing towards a complex situation in your waking life that needs problem-solving and courage.

title: Falling
entry: Falling off a building only to be saved by a friend.
analysis:
This dream can represent a number of different things depending on your personal life context. In general, falling in a dream might symbolize a feeling of losing control or fear of failure in some aspect of your waking life. It could reflect feelings of uncertainty or insecurities over a situation or decision. The building might represent a high ambition or goal that you've set for yourself.

Being saved by a friend in your dream can suggest that you may be relying on or seeking support from this person, or it might mean you'll need their help in some future situation. This could also symbolize a deep trust, appreciation, and connection with your friend.

However, the meaning of dreams can be very personal, and what they represent can vary greatly for each individual depending on their life experiences and current circumstances. These interpretations are general and may not necessarily apply to your specific situation. Reflect on your current life situation and emotional state to see if these interpretations make sense for you.

title: Funeral
entry: I was at my own funeral.
analysis: Dreaming about attending your own funeral might sound disturbing, but it's not necessarily a negative omen. It can suggest that you're undergoing a transformative phase in your life, where you're putting behind aspects of your old self and beginning a new chapter. You might be releasing old habits, attitudes, and relationships that no longer serve your growth. This dream can also reflect your feelings of sorrow and mourning over this change since it is a form of loss. Additionally, it may imply a desire for more attention, love, and validation from your loved ones.

title: Ocean
entry: I was swimming in the open ocean in the dark for endless miles.
analysis: The dream suggests that you are trying to navigate through an emotional or unclear part of your life. Swimming in open waters signifies exploration and discovery. If you feel no fear while swimming, it means you confidently face deep emotions and unconscious aspects of your personality. If you feel fear, you might be reluctant to confront these elements. The darkness could signify confusion or uncertainty about your path in life. Endless miles could mean that you're feeling a situation or problem in your life is ongoing, with no end in sight. Please remember that this analysis is subjective and it's essential to relate it to your personal circumstances for a more accurate interpretation.

title: Jungle
entry: I was part of a family who lived in the jungle thousands of years ago.
analysis: This dream appears to reflect a sense of origin or roots, signifying that you might be concentrated on your family connections, your ethnic or cultural heritage. The jungle aspect can portray a symbol of chaos and uncontrollability, possibly referring to aspects of your daily life that are chaotic or unpredictable. The fact it's set thousands of years ago might mean you're looking for simplicity or fundamental values in lifeâ€”that you might be feeling overwhelmed by technology or modern life worries. This sense of primordial living could also suggest a need for survival or expressing basic instincts. Could also suggest a yearning for a more natural, straightforward, and instinctive lifestyle.

title: Moon Explosion
entry:
Sitting on a hill, at night time.. There is a river maybe 50 feet down the hill and about 20 feet ahead of us there is a bunch of cat tails covering the ground that leads down to the river. It's a party type setting.. Feels like a 4th of July party... I'm sitting next to Cody and Darian.. Jake is there too but he went down into the brush to go find some people. There are also people all around us. 
We are sitting on the hill watching the moon... We are expecting the super moon to come any moment. When it finally starts to happen I get a rush of heavy intuition that something very big is about to happen. I could feel it see it smell it taste it touch it in the air. As soon as the moon starts weening into the red full super moon.. I knew what was going to happen. My entire vision became shaky.. And all of the sudden as I'm watching the moon progress... It explodes... Implodes... It was the most real thing you could ever imagine.. It may as well have really happened. I felt the heat from the explosion and the shift of gravity taking place on the earth. I realized in a few seconds what was really about to happen. That huge fire ball is about to evaporate our planet.. And if that doesn't do it... We are going to get knocked off of our gravitational path and the entire world will crack and scream. I knew I was going to die, and that every one around me was going to die. I look at Cody and Darian.. They are paralyzed in fear... I look down at the brush and see its on fire... I realize that Jake is in the brush... Thinking he's Already dead or dying.. This led me to turn around from the moon and close my eyes... Accept everything that is happening. I close my eyes and feeling the vibration of the shifting planet and the heat from the explosion, I make a wish to be with Abigail. I embody the feeling of death and I think about Abby in my assumed last moments... As soon as the thought hit and the second went by in which I was almost certain I would die, I get a warm burst of air hit my back.. A comforting warm burst... Soothing around the silhouette of my body.. 
I realize in this moment that I'm not going to die... I turn around and the adrenaline kicks in... I see Jake also coming out of the burning brush with a girl over his shoulder... Hauling his way out with sweet and blood. I shake Cody and Darian to see if they are ok.. They were responsive but in complete shock... I then, woke up
analysis:
Dreams are highly subjective, and interpretations can vary greatly depending on the individual's personal experiences, emotions, and associations. Here is a general analysis of your dream:

A hill often symbolizes a challenge or obstacle you are facing or about to face in your waking life. The night setting might indicate that this situation is concerning or unclear to you.

The river at the bottom of the hill could symbolize the flow of your emotions or life. It might mean you are going through a difficult or emotional situation.

The 4th of July party could represent a celebration, symbolizing enjoyment and relaxation. It could also signify your desire for more social activities and happiness in your life.

The super moon typically signifies completion, high power, and clarity. However, the moon exploding in this dream could represent that something highly impactful and disruptive is happening in your life, which is causing you a lot of distress and fear.

The fire could symbolize destruction, transformation, and strong emotions. You might be feeling overwhelmed and afraid of changes and challenges that are taking place in waking life.

Seeing your friends might indicate that you are thinking about them and they play an important role in your life. Your wish to be with Abigail could mean that you desire her comfort, support, or love during trying times.

Surviving the catastrophic event could suggest that even though you're facing great difficulties, you can overcome them and come out stronger. 

Remember, only you can truly interpret your dreams. Consider personal emotions, experiences, and current life situations when determining what your dream might mean to you.

title: Volcano
entry: Fell into a massive volcano and found elves at the bottom.
analysis:
It appears your dream contains several symbolic elements. Falling into a volcano may represent a situation in your waking life where you're entering a potentially dangerous or heated situation -- a circumstance that is unpredictable or volatile.

Discovering elves at the bottom of the volcano, meanwhile, can have different representations depending on your cultural background or personal beliefs. In general, elves are perceived as mystical creatures, often representing magic and wisdom. Encountering them in your dream might symbolize that you're discovering something unexpected, magical or wise within a risky, potentially destructive situation. 

Keep in mind, dreams are highly subjective and personal. These explanations are general interpretations and might not be wholly applicable to you. If the dream reflects or reminds you of any personal life situations, it's good to consider those perspectives as well.

title: Farm
entry: Lost on a farm at night, found a horse and rode it.
analysis:
The dream about being lost on a farm may symbolize a feeling of being out of place or experiencing confusion in your waking life. This could be a reflection of you trying to navigate through your subconscious issues or unresolved matters. The farm may signify hard work, persistence, and the fruits of your labor, hence, possible concerns about your productivity or efficiency.

The horse is a common symbol of strength, power, loyalty, and endurance. Finding a horse and riding it could represent your skill or ability to take control of certain situations. Despite the adversity (depicted by the darkness or night), you found a way to navigate â€“ possibly suggesting that you are capable enough to overcome your challenges or fears.

As dreams are very subjective, this interpretation may vary depending on the context and personal situation. It's always recommended to reflect on what these symbols relate to in your actual life to better understand the dream.

title: Highway
entry: I woke up in the middle of a busy highway on foot, dodging cars. I ended up jumping on one and riding it into NYC.
analysis:
Your dream seems to be combining several aspects of your subconscious thoughts, fears, and desires. 

Waking up in the middle of a busy highway suggests feelings of fear, chaos, and confusion in waking life. These might represent your current thoughts about how you're navigating through life or a situation that's chaotic, stressful and almost out of control. It could also signify living a fast-paced or high-pressure lifestyle where one mistake could be catastrophic.

Dodging the cars could potentially indicate that you are avoiding or handling many obstacles and challenges thrown in your way in real life. This act of a daring move can either stem from a feeling of desperation or growth in confidence and adeptness in dealing with difficulties.

Riding a car into NYC could be your subconsciousâ€™ message that despite the obstacles that may come your way, there is a decision or direction that will lead you to a place associated with energy, ambition, and new opportunities (symbolized by the representation of NYC as a land of dreams and growth).

Overall, this dream seems to be a strong message from your subconscious that even though you may face hard challenges, you have ample resilience and agility to handle and possibly overpower them. You're being directed towards bigger, better opportunities. You just need to keep faith and carry on.

title: Canyon
entry: I went to the Grand Canyon and fell down, but had a parachute.
analysis:
This dream can symbolize situations in your waking life where you might feel overwhelmed or out of control, similar to the fear and uncontrollable descent often related to falling in dreams. The Grand Canyon might symbolize a massive challenge or obstacle that you're facing or an experience that leaves you feeling small and insignificant.

However, having a parachute indicates that you have tools, abilities, or support systems in place that can help you navigate these challenges successfully. Even though you may experience negative scenarios, you're in some way prepared to handle them. This dream can be an affirmation of your resilience, preparedness, and ability to navigate through tough situations.
